xtce:Parameter.name: SCID_X285.PDU_SUBST_TLM_FLAG
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: PDU.SUBST_TLM_FLAG PDU:SUBST_TLM_FLAG Bit is always 0 in tlm from the Bridge FPGA. If substitute tlm is being created (or altered) by GSE, it must set this bit to 1 in order to differentiate substituted tlm from authentic tlm generated by the bridge FPGA. This bit is not writable. 0=PDU_TLM, 1=SUBST_TLM

xtce:Parameter.name: SCID_X285.PDU_A_B_INTERLOC
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: PDU.A_B_INTERLOC PDU:A_B_INTERLOC If a one is written to this bit, bridge output port a_b_interloc will drive a high logic value indefinitely, (until a zero is written to this register bit.). In SPP this output of the PDU is unused.

xtce:Parameter.name: SCID_X285.PDU_SEQ_FAILS_REG
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: PDU.SEQ_FAILS_REG PDU:SEQ_FAILS_REG A failsafe counter counts the number of FPGA clock cycles a command sequence uses, and if it exceeds a maximum value, the sequence execution will halt and the sequence controller state machine will reset. If this occurs, this seq_fails_reg bit will be set to 1

xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: FSW_CFDP.HK.TX_NAK_RCVD FSW_CFDP:TX_NAK_RCVD Count of the number of NAK PDUs received by the FSW regarding transmit transactions. NAKs indicate that the receiver detected missing data and requested retransmit of the missing data.

xtce:Parameter.name: SCID_X286.FSW_CFDP_HK_TX_FILE_DATA_SENT
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: FSW_CFDP.HK.TX_FILE_DATA_SENT FSW_CFDP:TX_FILE_DATA_SENT Count of the number of CFDP Transmit File Data PDUs produced. The transmission of a file consists of one or more file data PDUs that transmit the contents of the respective file.

xtce:Parameter.name: SCID_X286.FSW_CFDP_HK_TX_EOF_SENT
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: FSW_CFDP.HK.TX_EOF_SENT FSW_CFDP:TX_EOF_SENT Count of the number of CFDP Transmit End of File (EOF) PDUs generated. This PDU type is generated after sending the last file data PDU to tell the receiver that the entire file has been transmitted.

xtce:Parameter.name: SCID_X286.FSW_CFDP_HK_TX_ACK_SENT
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: FSW_CFDP.HK.TX_ACK_SENT FSW_CFDP:TX_ACK_SENT Count of the number of CFDP Transmit FIN ACK PDUs generated/transmitted. This is generated in response to receiving the FIN PDU from the recipient.

xtce:Parameter.name: SCID_X286.FSW_CFDP_HK_TX_EOF_TIMEOUTS
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: FSW_CFDP.HK.TX_EOF_TIMEOUTS FSW_CFDP:TX_EOF_TIMEOUTS Count of the number of timeouts while waiting for the EOF-ACK from the recipient. After sending an EOF, the sender expects an EOF-ACK. If it is not received within the timeout window, this counter is incremented and another EOF is produced.

xtce:Parameter.name: SCID_X286.HK_TX_TRANSACTION_TIMEOUTS
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: FSW_CFDP.HK.TX_TRANSACTION_TIMEOUTS FSW_CFDP:TX_TRANSACTION_TIMEOUTS Count of the number of CFDP Transmit transactions that have timed-out. A timed out transaction is declared as a transaction failure. The FSW will send another EOF and clear the transaction
